[2] Cholera - Sierra Leone (Western Area)
Date: Tue, 3 Oct 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and Concord Times (Freetown) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200610030656.html>

A severe cholera outbreak looms over Kissy, and Calaba Town environs,
medical sources reveal. Residents of Kissy, Rokupa, Wellington, Calaba and
Allen Towns in Freetown have been faced with a severe water crisis for the
past 1 month.
5 people have reportedly died at the Rokupa Government Hospital as a result
of the disease while over 200 people have been admitted at the hospital. A
senior nursing sister at the hospital who wants to remain anonymous said
the hospital is currently treating over 200 patients for cholera related
symptoms.
"We have found out that the communities where these patients are coming
from lack pure drinking water and decent toilet facilities," she asserted.
A resident of Rokupa explained that the environment lacks pure drinking
water, and infested with poor toilet facilities with piles of garbage
within the community. He pointed out that his uncle was experiencing
frequent stool and vomiting recently.
[Byline: Mohamed Massaquoi]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of Sierra Leone showing Freetown in the Western Area can be found at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/sierrale.pdf> - Mod.LL]
