[3] Cholera - Angola
Date: Fri, 29 Sep 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=476419>

45 new cholera cases were registered from 26 to 27 Sep 2006, in 15
provinces of the country, ANGOP learned Fri, 29 Sep 2006, from the Health
Ministry`s daily bulletin about the disease.
The cases, from which 2 resulted in death, happened in the provinces of
Bengo, Benguela, Bie, Cabinda, Kwanza-Norte, Kwanza-Sul, Luanda, Huambo,
Huila, Lunda-Norte, Malanje, Kuando Kubango, Namibe, Uige and Zaire.
In this period, the provinces with more cases were Namibe (10), Kwanza-Sul
and Bengo, with 7 cases each, and Kuando Kubango, with 5 cases. Zaire,
Huambo, Malanje, Lunda-Norte, Cabinda and Bie did not register any cases
during the referred period.
The communique reports cases detected since 13 Feb 2006, at the start of
the outbreak, until 27 Sep 2006 with 54 647 patients and 2223 deaths.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of Angola can be found at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/angola.pdf>
It is still not clear if the provinces of Cunene, Moxico, and Lunda Sul
have been affected. - Mod.LL])
