[4] Cholera - Angola (Huila)
Date: Thu, 5 Sep 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=477949>

Health authorities of Quipungo district, south Huila province, reported
that the 33 new cholera cases have claimed 10 lives in the past 8 days.
The fact was revealed to ANGOP this Thu, 5 Sep 2006, by the director of the
Municipal Health Section, Antonio Marcelino who informed that there has
been an increase of 3 deaths and 12 cases since the outbreak in the region.
Antonio Marcelino asked competent authorities of the province in order to
send medicines with urgency, as well as install tents to accommodate the
sick, because the single hospital in the region does not have the capacity
to attend to all patients. Among the efforts to fight against the disease,
the Municipal Health and Waters Department disinfected 12 wells, 8 water
reservoirs, and holds cleaning and rubbish collection campaigns.
The districts of Lubango, Quipungo and Matala are the mostly affected by
cholera, which has already killed 90 people.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
